Basic commands:
        terraform version
        terraform help
        terraform init
        terraform plan
        terraform apply / terraform apply -auto-approve
        terraform destroy / terraform destroy -auto-approve
        terraform fmt
        terraform validate ,checks the syntax
user_data in terraform: to install an app using script calling using a file option
ex: user_data = "${file(""install_httpd.sh)}"
httpd.sh == yum install httpd -y 
            systemctl start httpd
            http enable on
 To verify the result before execting use: terraform console
                                            enter the query to execute
                                            type exit to comeout
